County Council Meetings


Regular Meetings

Regular Council meetings are held twice monthly on Tuesdays at 5:00 pm, unless otherwise indicated.

Allegheny County Courthouse
4th Floor - Gold Room
436 Grant Street
Pittsburgh, PA 15219


Helpful Links

  • 2018 Regular Meeting Schedule
  • If you wish to speak, you must submit a Request to Comment.
  • Set up live streaming of County Council meetings.
  • Read verbatim regular meeting minutes.
  • View agendas, meeting details, notices and videos at Legistar.
  • You can also perform a Legislation Search on Legistar.Enter the bill number (listed on the agenda) to pull up the text of the bill.


Public Hearings

Council public hearings are held at 5:00 pm, as needed, unless otherwise indicated.

Allegheny County Courthouse
4th Floor - Gold Room
436 Grant Street
Pittsburgh, PA 15219


Helpful Links

  • If you wish to speak at a public hearing, you must submit a Request to Comment.
  • View agendas at Legistar.
  • Read verbatim public hearing minutes.


Committee Meetings

Committee meetings are held on Tuesdays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays, as needed, beginning at 4:00 pm.

Allegheny County Courthouse
Suite 119
436 Grant Street
Pittsburgh, PA 15219


Helpful Links

  • Council Committees and Members
  • If you wish to speak, you must submit a Request to Comment.
  • View agendas, action minutes, notices and videos at Legistar.

Give the Gift of Fun

Give the gift of fun with an Allegheny County Parks gift card.


Cards can be redeemed for activities throughout our nine parks - including skiing, snow tubing, golf, swimming, youth activities, Hartwood Acres tours, and more.
